                        <layout>
                           <p>Columns: 1;
                                                  ruled lines:  10 30;
                                                  written lines:  10 30; Pricking and ruling are visible. Watermark, iv recto, of a fleur-de-lis and the monogram 'B. W'. Watermark, [56], of the words 'Budgen &amp; Willmott'. The square and semi-cursive scripts are imitations of the Amsterdam letters and Rashi script respectively used in printing.Many marginal illuminations and illustrations, which consist mainly of gold and coloured designs.</p>
